{
  "workflow": {
    "id": 13735,
    "name": "Sync markdown files from Google Drive to Confluence pages automatically",
    "views": 85,
    "recentViews": 1,
    "totalViews": 85,
    "createdAt": "2026-02-26T14:36:09.316Z",
    "description": "## How it Works\nSave a .md file to the folder set in the triggers. This workflow will check every hour, convert the md file to HTML, and create a confluence page for it. If the md file is updated or changed in the folder, the workflow will check for a matching page in Confluence and update it.\n\n## Setup Steps\n* Ensure you have an Oauth2 connection set up with access to the Google Drive API.\n* Point to the folder in 'File Created' / 'File Updated' triggers\n* Create a scoped API token for Confluence with the 'write:confluence-content' and 'write:content:confluence' scopes, then add it as a header auth for your HTTP request nodes\n* Add your Confluence Cloud ID to the URL in \"Create Confluence Page\", \"Get Page ID\", and \"Update Confluence Page\"",
    "workflow": {
      "id": "6pqn4rVXEkn_2XS72k-8F",
      "meta": {
        "instanceId": "fdaaa8bf71e776295c225d845fce2e359a7cd45b0543c288355195ab06456418",
        "templateCredsSetupCompleted": true
      },
      "name": "Markdown to Confluence",
      "tags": [],
